  "synopsis": "Three 10-minute videos present a trippy view into the minds of their creators. Brought together by Pierre Taki of Denki Groove, Mechano: Scientific Attack Force features three shorts done in very different styles.\n\nThe three short films are:\n\n\"Plastic Gun Man\" - a 3D Western spoof\n\"World Meccano Triangle\" - a music video reminiscent of '90s era screensavers\n\"Haiirogaoka no Soridaijin\" (translated as \"Prime Minister of Gray Hill\") - an anime-style animated video parody of Akira Mochizuki's famous 1977 manga, Yuuhi ga Oka no Souri Daijin",
